5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN COMMANDMENTS IN
6 EACH PUBLIC SCHOOL BUILDING AND CLASSROOM; PROVIDING AN EXCEPTION FOR CERTAIN
7 SCHOOL DISTRICTS LOCATED ON OR NEAR AN INDIAN RESERVATION OR WITH MORE THAN ONE
8 AMERICAN INDIAN STUDENT ENROLLED IN THE DISTRICT; PROVIDING SPECIFICATIONS FOR THE
9 TEXT AND THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN COMMANDMENTS; AUTHORIZING A DISTRICT TO SPEND ITS
10 OWN FUNDS OR DONATED FUNDS TO PROVIDE THE DISPLAYS OR TO ACCEPT DONATED DISPLAYS;
11 EXCLUDING THE DISPLAY OF THE TEN COMMANDMENTS FROM THE PROHIBITION AGAINST
12 DISTRIBUTION OF SECTARIAN OR DENOMINATIONAL PUBLICATIONS IN A PUBLIC SCHOOL;
13 AMENDING SECTION 20-7-112, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE.”
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Required display of ten commandments. (1) The Except as provided
18 in subsection (2), the trustees of a district shall display the ten commandments in each school building and in
19 each classroom of each school in the district.
20 (2) Given the physical, mental, and sexual abuse that Native American children have suffered
21 while under the care of the federal government and the Catholic church, the requirements of this section do not
22 apply to a school district that is located on or near an Indian reservation or that has more than one American
23 Indian student enrolled in the district.
24 (3) The ten commandments must be displayed on a poster or framed document that is a minimum
25 size of 11 inches by 14 inches. The text of the ten commandments must be the central focus of the poster or
26 framed document and must be printed in a large, easily readable font.
27 (3)(4) The text of the display must read as follows:
